x4freetext: lead slowing-down neutron spectrometer at the Research
Reactor Institute, Kyoto University - lead cube of
1.5x1.5x1.5 m**3 assembled by 1600 lead blocks of
tantalum target are slowed down in lead.
Energy of the neutrons En at the time-of-travel
t in the lead was deduced from relation En=K/(t-t0)**2.
Slowing-down parameters K=175+-1 keV micros**2 and
t0=1.7+-0.1 microsec were obtained from a calibration
measurement using resonance filters, In (1.46 eV),
Au (4.91 eV), Co (132 eV), Cu (230 and 579 eV).
Fission fragments were discriminated from alphas
by the correlation between the pulse heights of the
first and the second anode signals.
For MA samples : by fitting the region between the
alphas and FF with two exponential functions, the
losses of the fission events and the contamination of
the alphas were estimated to be negligibly small <0.3%.
The selection efficiency of the fission events for
235U(A) was deduced by comparing the fission-yield
ratio 245Cm/235U obtained using two 235U samples and
estimated to be (58.1+-0.2)% when the pulse-height
Fission fragments are detected with MLPPAC -
